OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FContingency plans to cover special
OL,7,Fschool summer schemes are being
OL,8,Fexamined, the Stormont's Health
OL,9,FMinister said, after it was announced
OL,10,Fthat the programme would be called off
OL,11,Fthis year.
OL,13,FIt emerged on Thursday that the
OL,14,Fschemes, which provide support for
OL,15,Fchildren with additional needs over
OL,16,Fthe summer, would not go ahead in 2026
OL,17,Fover concerns about the healthcare
OL,18,Favailable for pupils.
OL,20,FAn Assembly committee heard families
OL,21,Fare "spitting fire" over the decision.
OL,26,@}D@EOU}D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FThe Education Authority said it had
OL,7,Fattempted to avoid the move through
OL,8,Frepeated engagement with the
OL,9,FDepartment of Health.
OL,11,FIt said it had "made clear" that on-
OL,12,Fsite nursing cover would be required
OL,13,Ffor summer schemes to be held safely.
OL,15,FHowever, the authority said the
OL,16,Fdepartment had confirmed this will not
OL,17,Fbe available.
OL,19,FIn a statement, the Education
OL,20,FAuthority said: "This decision has
OL,21,Fbeen taken solely on safety grounds.
OL,26,@sD@POUsD@[O]|D@QOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,F"We deeply regret it and fully
OL,7,Funderstand that it will be very
OL,8,Fdistressing for children and parents."
OL,10,FThe authority acknowledged the
OL,11,Fpressures facing the health service,
OL,12,Fand said it would continue to work to
OL,13,Fresolve the issue of healthcare
OL,14,Fprovision for special school pupils.
OL,16,FIt said its view was that "consistent
OL,17,Fprovince-wide and year-round nurse-led
OL,18,Fprovision for all special schools is
OL,19,Frequired".
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@fO]xD@[OU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FIt added: "Its current absence, in the
OL,7,Fcontext of greater complexity of
OL,8,Fhealth needs, has created growing
OL,9,Fpressures and concerns for the welfare
OL,10,Fof children in term time.
OL,12,F"The risks are much greater in the
OL,13,Fsummer months when there is inevitably
OL,14,Freduced staffing availability for
OL,15,Fsummer schemes, with the schools
OL,16,Fthemselves being closed."
OL,26,@nD@KOUtD@AOUxD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FAt the Assembly's Health Committee on
OL,7,FThursday, SDLP MLA Colin McGrath said
OL,8,F"that little bit of comfort for
OL,9,Fparents" and "opportunity for those
OL,10,Fchildren" had been "thrown away".
OL,12,FHe said "those summer schemes must
OL,13,Fhappen" and added that families were
OL,14,F"spitting fire" over the decision.
OL,16,FHe questioned the minister on what
OL,17,Fwould be done for vulnerable children
OL,18,Fwho will have two months without
OL,19,Fstructured activity due to "cutbacks
OL,20,Ffrom the Department of Health".
OL,26,@pD@AOUqD@HO]qD@NOUrD@IO]rD@TOUrD@`O]tD@
OL,26,AIOUuD@GO]vD@AOUvD@OO]{D@\OU|D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FHealth Minister Mike Nesbitt said the
OL,7,Fprogramme was a two-week scheme, but
OL,8,FMr McGrath replied that the school
OL,9,Fbreak means children go two months
OL,10,Fwithout provision.
OL,12,FThe minister told the committee: "We
OL,13,Fare looking at contingency plans to
OL,14,Fcover that period.
OL,16,F"But I think it's just very
OL,17,Fdisappointing that those summer
OL,18,Fschools are being suspended."
OL,26,@tD@bOUxD@AOUzD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FThe UUP MLA said he was "trying to
OL,7,Funderstand" what has changed since
OL,8,Flast year and added he was "surprised
OL,9,Fto hear that announcement coming
OL,10,Ftoday".
OL,12,FMr Nesbitt said one of the issues is
OL,13,Fthat the Department of Education, led
OL,14,Fby DUP minister Paul Givan, was "not
OL,15,Faware of the qualifications of all
OL,16,Ftheir classroom assistants".
OL,18,FHe said he had proposed that such
OL,19,Fassistants on 52-week contracts could
OL,20,Fbe switched to look after summer
OL,21,Fschemes.
OL,26,@nD@YOUoD@KO]pD@\OUrD@FO]vD@aOUxD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FMr Nesbitt said: "I'm not quite sure
OL,7,Fwhy we have given up so early on with
OL,8,Fthe summer still some months away."
OL,10,FMr McGrath said it sounded like Mr
OL,11,FNesbitt was having "a bit of a row"
OL,12,Fwith and "passing the buck" to the
OL,13,FEducation Minister over the terms of
OL,14,Fclassroom assistants.
OL,16,FMr Nesbitt said the characterisation
OL,17,Fwas "deeply unfair" and "just wrong".
OL,26,@nD@ROUpD@cO]sD@TOUsD@cO]tD@JOUtD@[O]yD@
OL,26,AEOUyD@SO]yD@YOUyD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,F"I'm saying that an official from the
OL,7,FDepartment of Education said they
OL,8,Fdidn't have full knowledge of the
OL,9,Fqualifications of the classroom
OL,10,Fassistants.
OL,12,F"That's just a fact ` that's not
OL,13,Fpoking at anybody."
OL,15,FMr McGrath replied: "It's farcical
OL,16,Fthat one end of our Executive doesn't
OL,17,Fknow what the other is doing, and in
OL,18,Fone end of the Executive, you're
OL,19,Fsaying the staff don't even know the
OL,20,Fqualifications of the staff that work
OL,21,Ffor them."
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUuD@SO]wD@UOU}D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FSinn Fein's Cathy Mason called for
OL,7,Fministers to "find a solution".
OL,9,FIn a statement she said: "It is
OL,10,Funacceptable that the health and
OL,11,Feducation ministers could not come up
OL,12,Fwith a solution to continue this much-
OL,13,Fneeded provision this summer.
OL,15,F"These special school summer schemes
OL,16,Fare a lifeline for many families,
OL,17,Fproviding vital respite and important
OL,18,Fsupport for children with complex
OL,19,Fneeds.
OL,26,@nD@GrroD@NOUoD@^O]qD@ZOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,F"In recent days we have seen the
OL,7,FEducation Minister attempt to deflect
OL,8,Ffrom his failings in improving the
OL,9,Feducation system. Instead he should be
OL,10,Ffocused on protecting the most
OL,11,Fvulnerable in our society.
OL,13,F"I will be writing to both ministers
OL,14,Fto challenge this decision and to
OL,15,Fpress them to get their heads together
OL,16,Fand find a solution that works for
OL,17,Fthese children, their families and
OL,18,Ftheir schools."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUzD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/13
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,445,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1774620679
OL,3,CFamilies 'spitting fire' over summer
OL,4,Cscheme decision
OL,6,FTUV councillor Matthew Armstrong, who
OL,7,Fis the father of a child with
OL,8,Fadditional needs, said the schemes are
OL,9,Fa "vital part of the holiday season"
OL,10,Fand described the announcement as
OL,11,F"totally unacceptable".
OL,13,FThe Ballymena representative added:
OL,14,F"Whatever the truth, and whoever to
OL,15,Fblame, it is outrageous and leaves
OL,16,Fsome of the most vulnerable children
OL,17,Fin society in the lurch."
OL,19,FCatch up with the latest UTV Live on
